'Massive thanks from everyone. @briewhelan was a superstar. Everyone is doing amazingly well. Couldn't be happier,' Attwood said on his official Twitter account.

After rushing off to attend the birth of his child, it was expected that he would only make the bench for Saturday's game. 

However, it now seems as though Attwood will partner Courtney Lawes in the second row against the All Blacks with the uncapped George Kruis of Saracens offering cover from the bench.  

